{
  "name": "RPlog_When_Caspians_Attack_Part_1",
  "title": "Storm at the Plaxton Embassy",
  "summary": "On Caspar, the Empire exploits days of mounting Sarian unrest in Plaxton City, manipulating a protest outside the New Republic Embassy into a full-scale riot while Imperial Storm Commandos under Commander Calyx Drogyn prepare a rooftop assault. Roused from sleep, Ambassador Ambrosia Delgard entrusts her daughter Gabi to the Jedi Leo Corak, who carries the child toward an escape as the landing pad falls and the gates are breached. Drogyn's snipers pick off rooftop marines and his commandos grapple across to the embassy roof, sabotaging the turbolifts as protesters and Imperial troops pour in from below and above. Rather than flee, Ambrosia commandeers the holoterminals to broadcast the unfolding atrocity galaxy-wide, exposing the manipulators before her feeds are destroyed. Leo escapes out a washroom window into the forest with Gabi clinging to his back, while the embassy's marines mount a doomed defense, leaving the outcome unresolved as the log breaks to be continued.",
